Carol Midgley
Published at 12:01AM, December 5 2012
Rebecca Sinclair has moved house 17 times in 27 years of marriage. Her high-ranking US Army commander husband has been home for five of the past 11 years — and now faces charges of sexual misconduct. We shouldn’t be surprised, she tells Carol Midgley
As a seasoned army wife Rebecca Sinclair might have been expected to remain quietly in the background when her husband was accused of sexual misconduct. Instead, she took out her pen. The magnificent article that she wrote for The Washington Post did not excuse her husband’s infidelity or suggest that the allegations shouldn’t be investigated, but it did expose the fractured, transient and dysfunctional lives that military families are forced to lead. In 800 measured words, Mrs Sinclair, a mother of two, left the reader marvelling that any modern military marriages survive at all.
