Richard Holbrooke: "Will be remembered for his tireless diplomacy, love of country and pursuit of peace," said President Obama
Catherine Philp
Washington
Last updated at 12:01AM, December 15 2010
President Obama hailed Richard Holbrooke as a “true giant of American foreign policy” yesterday, leading an outpouring of tributes as news of his death spread across the globe.
Mr Holbrooke, who was serving as Mr Obama’s special envoy to Afghanistan and Pakistan, died on Monday night after emergency heart surgery. He was 69. He had been in a critical condition since collapsing during a meeting with Hillary Clinton, the Secretary of State, on Friday.
Mr Obama described him as “a truly unique figure who will be remembered for his tireless diplomacy, love of country and pursuit of peace”.
